105
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:43,950
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

106
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:56,563
But Mr. Matjjigae,
you quit drinking, right?

107
00:04:57,164 --> 00:04:59,800
I thought you wouldn't be able to go
to Korean street stalls

108
00:04:59,866 --> 00:05:01,635
or Japanese izakayas anymore.

109
00:05:01,701 --> 00:05:03,904
-I can go there.
-Really?

110
00:05:03,970 --> 00:05:06,773
In Japan, we can have

111
00:05:06,873 --> 00:05:09,042
-non-alcoholic drinks.
-That's different.

112
00:05:09,109 --> 00:05:10,944
Back then, in Japan too,
if you didn't drink…

113
00:05:11,011 --> 00:05:13,713
Yeah, there was a time when
not drinking felt a bit out of place.

114
00:05:13,780 --> 00:05:15,916
Almost everyone drank.

115
00:05:15,982 --> 00:05:19,219
Mr. Kuroda, it's okay to just have
non-alcoholic drinks these days.

116
00:05:19,286 --> 00:05:20,453
Things have changed.

117
00:05:20,854 --> 00:05:22,856
-Times have changed.
-Yes.

118
00:05:24,858 --> 00:05:27,694
So, 20 years ago,
how much did Mr. Matjjigae drink?

119
00:05:27,761 --> 00:05:30,197
Since they drank together,
a bottle would be gone in no time.

120
00:05:30,263 --> 00:05:31,298
In no time.

121
00:05:31,364 --> 00:05:34,734
Mr. Matjjigae didn't really eat much.
He mostly just drank.

122
00:05:35,535 --> 00:05:37,437
-That's pretty cool.
-Cool? Hardly…

123
00:05:37,504 --> 00:05:38,705
Like a samurai.

124
00:05:38,772 --> 00:05:41,408
-But…
-But when he got sleepy, he left first.

125
00:05:41,474 --> 00:05:44,311
Yes. The hotel was next door,
so I'd say, "I'm heading out," and go.

126
00:05:44,377 --> 00:05:47,247
And he always paid the bill,

127
00:05:47,314 --> 00:05:49,416
so everyone would be disappointed
when he left.

128
00:05:49,482 --> 00:05:53,887
That was part of playing
the father's role.

129
00:05:53,954 --> 00:05:55,155
It couldn't be helped.

130
00:05:57,958 --> 00:05:59,659
There are so many different dishes.

131
00:05:59,726 --> 00:06:01,027
Yes.

132
00:06:01,094 --> 00:06:03,029
First, try the shutō…

133
00:06:03,096 --> 00:06:06,900
-And mascarpone cheese.
-It's a must-have.

134
00:06:06,967 --> 00:06:11,004
This place is actually the creator
of shutō with mascarpone cheese.

135
00:06:11,071 --> 00:06:12,339
-We'll have that.
-Okay.

136
00:06:12,405 --> 00:06:14,741
COURSE 1: THE OWNER'S ORIGINAL CREATION

137
00:06:14,808 --> 00:06:19,166
SHUTŌ (JAPANESE-STYLE SALTED SEAFOOD)
WITH MASCARPONE CHEESE

138
00:06:19,316 --> 00:06:22,649
Normally, shutō is mixed
with cream cheese, right?

139
00:06:22,716 --> 00:06:26,786
The combination of cream cheese
and salted seafood already existed.

140
00:06:26,853 --> 00:06:28,655
-Right?
-But I didn't like

141
00:06:28,722 --> 00:06:31,858
how firm cream cheese was.

142
00:06:32,359 --> 00:06:35,962
I wanted something smoother,
so I started using mascarpone instead.

143
00:06:37,631 --> 00:06:41,534
That was about 20 years ago,
back when it wasn't popular at all.

144
00:06:41,601 --> 00:06:44,137
I tried it here
and thought it was delicious.

145
00:06:44,204 --> 00:06:45,972
Then, while you were filming a drama,

146
00:06:46,039 --> 00:06:48,275
you mentioned it on another show,

147
00:06:48,341 --> 00:06:50,543
and the dish spread all across Japan.

148
00:06:50,610 --> 00:06:55,148
I mentioned how good it was
on TV several times.

149
00:06:55,815 --> 00:06:57,350
-You mentioned this restaurant?
-Then

150
00:06:57,417 --> 00:07:00,887
the menu spread
all over Japan, apparently.

151
00:07:00,954 --> 00:07:03,290
Is the shutō the regular kind?

152
00:07:03,823 --> 00:07:04,691
It's tuna.

153
00:07:04,758 --> 00:07:05,625
-Tuna.
-Tuna?

154
00:07:05,692 --> 00:07:10,397
Yes, our restaurant specialized
in tuna back then,

155
00:07:11,064 --> 00:07:14,034
so we used tuna shutō.

156
00:07:14,567 --> 00:07:17,958
MASCARPONE CHEESE

157
00:07:18,338 --> 00:07:21,161
