158
00:07:24,577 --> 00:07:26,613
This is our shutō
with mascarpone cheese.

159
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:29,149
-With tuna shutō.
-Shall we

160
00:07:29,215 --> 00:07:31,584
-give it a try?
-Yes.

161
00:07:31,651 --> 00:07:34,207
SHUTŌ AND MASCARPONE
4,000 WON, 440 YEN

162
00:07:34,716 --> 00:07:36,089
SHUTŌ AND MASCARPONE

163
00:07:36,156 --> 00:07:38,024
TUNA SHUTŌ WITH MASCARPONE,
NOT CREAM CHEESE

164
00:07:38,091 --> 00:07:39,726
AN APPETIZER THAT SHOWS THE OWNER'S FLAIR

165
00:07:40,493 --> 00:07:43,129
This is my first time trying mascarpone
in a combination like this.

166
00:07:43,196 --> 00:07:44,998
I've only ever used it

167
00:07:45,065 --> 00:07:48,835
for making tiramisu.

168
00:07:53,707 --> 00:07:55,942
-They go really well together.
-Right?

169
00:07:57,644 --> 00:07:59,546
It's incredibly good.

170
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:01,815
-I told you.
-The sesame seeds…

171
00:08:01,881 --> 00:08:04,250
They're a brilliant touch.

172
00:08:04,317 --> 00:08:08,488
It's that sweet and salty balance.
The mascarpone is sweet and smooth,

173
00:08:08,555 --> 00:08:11,658
and it completely rounds out
the saltiness of the tuna shutō.

174
00:08:17,464 --> 00:08:19,265
This calls for sake.

175
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:21,234
Should we order some?

176
00:08:21,301 --> 00:08:22,736
Do you have any recommendations?

177
00:08:22,802 --> 00:08:26,639
Summer sake has just started coming in.

178
00:08:26,706 --> 00:08:28,408
This is Yamagata Masamune.

179
00:08:28,475 --> 00:08:30,643
Summer sake goes down easily.

180
00:08:30,710 --> 00:08:32,545
-It's hot, so I'll have summer sake.
-Okay.

181
00:08:32,612 --> 00:08:33,513
Yes.

182
00:08:33,580 --> 00:08:36,616
There's that Homura logo.

183
00:08:37,217 --> 00:08:38,718
-It's been so long.
-This…

184
00:08:38,785 --> 00:08:40,954
Homura means "flame."

185
00:08:41,021 --> 00:08:43,323
HOMURA (FLAME) LOGO

186
00:08:43,390 --> 00:08:44,724
Thank you.

187
00:08:49,462 --> 00:08:50,697
This is good.

188
00:08:50,764 --> 00:08:51,731
It's good?

189
00:08:51,798 --> 00:08:53,633
It's fresh,

190
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:56,803
with a fruity note.

191
00:08:57,971 --> 00:08:59,672
-Try pairing it.
-It's perfect.

192
00:09:10,350 --> 00:09:11,484
-It's good.
-It's good?

193
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:15,555
Drinking it right after the mascarpone
makes it feel extra smooth.

194
00:09:16,489 --> 00:09:19,492
It's almost like rich milk ice cream.

195
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:22,062
And what else?

196
00:09:22,862 --> 00:09:27,067
There are quite a few
Okinawan dishes here.

197
00:09:28,034 --> 00:09:31,204
Like tebichi or goya champuru.

198
00:09:31,271 --> 00:09:34,074
-Make it in your style, Mr. Kuroda.
-Right.

199
00:09:34,140 --> 00:09:35,208
What's yaki tebichi?

200
00:09:35,275 --> 00:09:37,477
Tebichi means pigs' feet.

201
00:09:37,544 --> 00:09:38,978
YAKI TEBICHI
GRILLED PIGS' FEET

202
00:09:39,045 --> 00:09:40,447
Pigs' feet sound good.

203
00:09:40,513 --> 00:09:43,083
-Shall we have the tebichi?
-Tebichi. Okay.

204
00:09:43,149 --> 00:09:46,152
And maybe something for him…

205
00:09:46,219 --> 00:09:48,421
There's rafute,
a Japanese-style braised pork.

206
00:09:48,488 --> 00:09:49,656
Japanese-style braised pork?

207
00:09:49,722 --> 00:09:52,325
Yes, rafute is an Okinawan pork dish,
seasoned with brown sugar.

208
00:09:52,392 --> 00:09:56,029
It's a sweet, savory
Japanese-style braised pork. It's good.

209
00:09:56,096 --> 00:09:59,299
-And for the finale, there's pepe-meshi.
-Pepe-meshi.

210
00:09:59,365 --> 00:10:00,934
-He's been talking about it.
-Yes.

211
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:03,670
"There's something called pepe-meshi."

212
00:10:03,736 --> 00:10:05,338
"What's pepe-meshi?"

213
00:10:05,405 --> 00:10:07,373
"You won't know
until you try it yourself."

214
00:10:07,807 --> 00:10:09,342
-We're not at the finale yet.
-Yes.

215
00:10:09,409 --> 00:10:11,077
Then I'll have the kakuni,
the braised pork.

216
00:10:11,144 --> 00:10:12,846
-Kakuni.
-Please.

217
00:10:13,413 --> 00:10:14,881
COURSE 2: OKINAWAN FUSION DISH

218
00:10:14,948 --> 00:10:17,150
YAKI TEBICHI (GRILLED PIGS' FEET)

219
00:10:17,217 --> 00:10:20,954
YAKI RAFUTE
(OKINAWAN-STYLE BROWN SUGAR BRAISED PORK)

220
00:10:21,020 --> 00:10:23,990
Why have you always had
so many Okinawan dishes here?

221
00:10:24,057 --> 00:10:28,928
I originally started out
specializing in tuna,

222
00:10:28,995 --> 00:10:32,832
but my tuna supplier closed down.
So when I looked for new ones,

223
00:10:32,899 --> 00:10:38,204
most of the tuna wholesalers had started
running their own restaurants.

224
00:10:38,271 --> 00:10:40,840
There wasn't anyone left
to supply me with tuna.

225
00:10:40,907 --> 00:10:44,144
-I thought it was over.
-Right.

226
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:47,814
But I had a liquor supplier
down in Okinawa.

227
00:10:47,881 --> 00:10:49,949
The old man there told me,

228
00:10:50,016 --> 00:10:53,219
"If things get tough,
try making Okinawan food."

229
00:10:53,286 --> 00:10:58,158
"I'll help you with anything.
I'll send you whatever you need."

230
00:10:58,224 --> 00:11:00,293
So after I closed my restaurant for a bit,

231
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:03,630
I went to stay at his place

232
00:11:03,696 --> 00:11:07,967
for a few weeks.
He took me all over Okinawa,

233
00:11:08,034 --> 00:11:10,637
saying things like,
"This is Okinawan culture,"

234
00:11:10,703 --> 00:11:13,573
and, "This sells well in Okinawa."

235
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:15,552
Then when we came home,
his wife would be waiting,

236
00:11:15,652 --> 00:11:18,011
and she taught me how to cook
Okinawan home-style dishes.

237
00:11:18,077 --> 00:11:20,113
-Really? That's incredible.
-That's amazing.

238
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:22,749
-I got back on my feet.
-You could make a drama about it.

239
00:11:22,815 --> 00:11:25,852
That was about 20 years ago.

240
00:11:25,919 --> 00:11:26,819
That's awesome.

241
00:11:26,886 --> 00:11:29,322
-Yes.
-Here you go. Yaki tebichi.

242
00:11:30,190 --> 00:11:31,991
-Please put the bones in this bowl.
